    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As we now have independent widgets in the documentation, it means that no `hits` widget were loaded before the `hitsPerPageSelector` that could set the `hitsPerPage` value of the helper state.\n\nThe `hitsPerPageSelector` currently silently ignore the error, and thus does not auto-select any of the passed values. If a `hitsPerPage` exists, it select the corresponding value in the dropdown or throw an error if none matches.\n\nI suggest that we change this behavior and that if no `hitsPerPage` is previously set, we set it to the first value of the dropdown. We'll have to make sure the order in which `hits` and `hitsPerPageSelector` are started is irrelevant.\n\nIn a nutshell, here what I suggest, in pseudo-code:\n\n``` javascript\n// Case 1\nhitsWidget(hitsPerPage: 6);\nhitsPerPageWidget(); // Select the value 6 if in the list, throw an error if no such value\n\n// Case 2\nhitsPerPageWidget(); // Select the first value of the list and set it as hitsPerPage\n\n// Case 3\nhitsPerPageWidget(); // Select first value of the list and set it as hitsPerPage\nhitsWidget(hitsPerPage: 6); // Changes the hitsPerPage value. Updates the dropdown selected value if in the list, throw an error otherwise\n```\n\nWDYT?\n",
    "created_at": "2015-11-10T13:21:27Z",
